328459952509224250.String:
Eu entendo que a Vampira lhe deu uma cartilha sobre a ascensão de mutantes no século 20. Agora é a minha vez de dizer-lhe sobre os eventos mais recentes.

Em um ponto, há alguns anos, as pessoas estimaram a população total de mutantes em algo que se aproxima de um milhão em todo o mundo. Para alguns seres humanos, deve ter parecido como um mutante vivendo em cada esquina, e eu imagino que mais do que algumas pessoas sentiram que seu mundo familiar foi se esvaindo.

Enquanto isso, os mutantes se veem diante de uma ampla gama de ameaças. Várias encarnações do __PROTECTED_0__Brotherhood of Evil Mutants__PROTECTED_1__ surgiram. O __PROTECTED_2__Hellfire Club__PROTECTED_3__ tentou recrutar Jean Grey mas transformou-a na destruidora Fênix Negra. Vilões como o Senhor Sinistro,  a Rainha dos Duendes, Mojo, o Rei das Sombras, Stryfe e Apocalypse tentaram destruir os X-Men e arruinaram o meu sonho de co-existência pacífica.

De alguma forma, os X-Men suportaram tudo. A equipe cresceu e evoluiu de seus cinco membros originais. Perdemos alguns amigos ao longo do caminho, mas nós também ganhamos novos também.

Espero que esse seja o ponto do plano de aula de Dani. Os mutantes podem ser o próximo passo da evolução humana, mas também temos de aprender a nos adaptar a um mundo em constante mudança, evoluindo para enfrentar os novos desafios que possam surgir.

Tudo bem, eu acredito que isso seja o suficiente de aulas de história hoje. Por que você não volta para a missão __PROTECTED_4__Dani Moonstar__PROTECTED_5__ e ver se as histórias que você aprendeu vão manter a classe ocupada?

Missões Lendárias ficam disponíveis no nível 20, e permitem viajar pelo universo Marvel Heroes completando objetivos únicos para ganhar XP e __PROTECTED_2__'Marcas de Odin'__PROTECTED_3__!

__PROTECTED_10__Terminais__PROTECTED_11__

Disponíveis no nível 20, Terminais são áreas menores de supervilões da história. Podem ser jogados quantas vezes que quiser, e alguns chefes até possuem itens exclusivos! Terminais vêm de três formas: __PROTECTED_12__Verde__PROTECTED_13__ (dificuldade normal), __PROTECTED_14__Vermelho__PROTECTED_15__ (muito difícil) e __PROTECTED_16__Cósmico__PROTECTED_17__ (muito difícil, só após o nível 60.)

Completar um terminal te dará um __PROTECTED_18__Caco de Cubo__PROTECTED_19__ a cada 24 horas. Estes Cacos de Cubo são gastos na vendedora Cléa na Torre dos Vingadores, em itens especiais que incluem receitas de criação.

__PROTECTED_20__X-Defesa__PROTECTED_21__

A X-Defesa é um modo de jogo onde jogadores precisam defender os alunos da Mansão X de ondas constantes de inimigos.

Para cada onda completada, a força dos inimigos aumenta consideravelmente, assim como as recompensas! No fim da sessão, um baú de tesouro final surgirá com recompensas baseadas no seu desempenho. Entre na X-Defesa pela aba __PROTECTED_22__Desafios__PROTECTED_23__ de Ponto de Passagem.

__PROTECTED_24__Holo-Simulador da SHIELD__PROTECTED_25__

O Holo-Simulador da SHIELD é um modo para 1 ou 2 jogadores que possui muitas ondas únicas de inimigos e objetivos, incluindo uma batalha com uma versão holográfica do Hulk! Como a X-Defesa, a dificuldade e as recompensas aumentam com cada onda.

Este modo também é acessível pela aba __PROTECTED_26__Desafios__PROTECTED_27__ de Ponto de Passagem.

__PROTECTED_28__Patrulhas__PROTECTED_29__

Patrulhas são um modo de jogo aberto que permite heróis patrulharem as ruas do universo Marvel Heroes, completando objetivos como derrotar ondas de supervilões, impedir assaltos a bancos, e combater quase todo tipo de capanga ou robô assassino no Universo Marvel!

Entre nas Patrulhas pela aba __PROTECTED_30__Desafios__PROTECTED_31__ de Ponto de Passagem.

__PROTECTED_32__Isso não é Tudo...__PROTECTED_33__

Estamos sempre adicionando novas mecânicas e modos de jogo, então fique de olho no site __PROTECTED_34__MarvelHeroes.com__PROTECTED_35__ para saber das novidades e notícias semanais!

548163889168909574.String: Victor von Doom não teve uma vida fácil. Nascido na Latvéria, a mãe de Victor foi reivindicada pelo demônio Mefisto em um acordo místico que deu errado. A perda de sua mãe foi a chave da motivação de Victor, levando-o à excelência no estudo de todas as formas possíveis de libertá-la das garras de Mefisto: científicas ou místicas. Seus estudos eventualmente o levaram à Universidade Estadual de Nova York, junto com Reed Richards e Ben Grimm. Ao construir uma máquina para salvar sua mãe, Victor foi pego em uma explosão sobre a qual Reed Richards o havia alertado. Expulso e com sua face desfigurada, Victor von Doom culparia para sempre o futuro Senhor Fantástico por suas próprias falhas. Mesmo após tomar controle sobre sua terra natal na Latvéria para utilizar seus recursos em seus planos, isso não foi o suficiente para ele. Apenas a humilhação do maldito Richards e a dominação global completa saciaria o apetite do Doutor Destino!

__PROTECTED_9__BATTLE YOUR WAY THROUGH THE MARVEL UNIVERSE!__PROTECTED_10__

In Marvel Heroes, you take the role of an iconic character from the Marvel Universe to fight villains and thwart evil plans.

The information on this page should help you master the basics of Marvel Heroes, but it's not a complete reference to every detail of the game.

You can find more information on __PROTECTED_11__blue highlighted game terms__PROTECTED_12__ on the Glossary tab of the Help screen.


__PROTECTED_13__Click to MOVE__PROTECTED_14__
Move by __PROTECTED_15__left-clicking__PROTECTED_16__ a location. If you hold the __PROTECTED_17__left mouse button__PROTECTED_18__ or the __PROTECTED_19__W__PROTECTED_20__ key, you'll move continuously in the direction of your pointer.


__PROTECTED_21__Click to ATTACK__PROTECTED_22__
Click on enemies to attack them. __PROTECTED_0__ activates the power assigned to your left mouse button, while __PROTECTED_1__ activates the power assigned to your right mouse button.


__PROTECTED_23__Gamepad: Target Indicator__PROTECTED_24__
A __PROTECTED_299__ shader on an enemy indicates the current focus of your hero. This target indicator will not force all attacks (like dash) towards the enemy, but is a great way of knowing where most attacks are about to be directed.

__PROTECTED_25__Gamepad: Target-Lock__PROTECTED_26__
Press (Gamepad: Right Bumper Button (R1)) to toggle on Target-Lock mode. The target indicator will not move from that enemy until it is defeated or Target Lock is turned off. 

__PROTECTED_27__Tip! Gamepad: Target Assist__PROTECTED_28__
With an enemy Target Locked, tilt Right-Stick in the direction of another enemy and the Target Lock will move to that enemy. It's a quick way to target a specific enemy. You can even Lock on to a target behind you by holding the Right-Stick in that direction before toggling on Target-Lock.


__PROTECTED_29__Tip! Forced stop__PROTECTED_30__
To attack without accidentally moving, hold __PROTECTED_31__SHIFT__PROTECTED_32__ when attacking. This is really useful with ranged attacks!  If using a gamepad you will automatically stop to fire attacks.


__PROTECTED_33__Tip! Forced move__PROTECTED_34__
To guarantee that you move to a specific location, hold __PROTECTED_35__CTRL__PROTECTED_36__ when you __PROTECTED_37__left-click__PROTECTED_38__. You will move without attacking, even if you click on an enemy. Gamepad players may just move there without initiating an attack.


__PROTECTED_39__Tip! Hold down to attack continuously__PROTECTED_40__
Many attacks fire repeatedly as long as you hold down the button for that attack.


__PROTECTED_41__Fuels for Your Powers__PROTECTED_42__
All heroes have a circle towards the bottom right of the screen showing your __PROTECTED_43__resource__PROTECTED_44__, which represents your hero's inner store of energy. Check your hero's __PROTECTED_45__Traits__PROTECTED_46__ in your __PROTECTED_47__Powers Library__PROTECTED_48__ to understand what fuels your hero. 

__PROTECTED_49__Tip! Not every hero uses Spirit__PROTECTED_50__
Deadpool has no resource and all of his powers are free!

__PROTECTED_51__Tip! Secondary resources__PROTECTED_52__
Some heroes have a __PROTECTED_53__secondary resource__PROTECTED_54__, which is named differently for each hero. Secondary resources are automatically expended when appropriate to augment the effects of your powers. Examine your hero's power panel for more information about their secondary resource.


__PROTECTED_55__Basic Powers__PROTECTED_56__
Every Hero starts with at least one Basic Attack. (Default __PROTECTED_2__.) Powers marked as __PROTECTED_57__Basic Powers__PROTECTED_58__ don't cost spirit. It's a means of staying in the action for Heroes that need a spirit recharge.


__PROTECTED_59__HEALTH Keeps You in the Fight__PROTECTED_60__
The __PROTECTED_300__ circle towards the bottom left of the screen indicates your __PROTECTED_61__health__PROTECTED_62__, which represents how much damage your hero can take before being defeated.


Be careful when you see the screen flashing __PROTECTED_301__: your health is getting low! You can regain health by picking up __PROTECTED_302__ or purple orbs, or by using your __PROTECTED_63__S.H.I.E.L.D. Med Kit__PROTECTED_64__ ability (Default Key(__PROTECTED_3__) / Gamepad (Left Bumper Button) )


__PROTECTED_65__Tip! __PROTECTED_289__. Med Kit__PROTECTED_66__
Your Med Kit is extremely useful and will often save your life! Be sure to familiarize yourself with the Med Kit on your __PROTECTED_67__action bar__PROTECTED_68__ so you can quickly and easily use it in emergencies. Your Med Kits will never run out, but they need a moment to resupply after each use.

__PROTECTED_69__DEFEAT is Temporary__PROTECTED_70__
If your health reaches zero, your hero is __PROTECTED_71__defeated__PROTECTED_72__. When this happens, you have two options:
- Return to the last __PROTECTED_73__waypoint__PROTECTED_74__ you crossed.
- Wait to see if you'll be __PROTECTED_75__revived__PROTECTED_76__ by another hero. You can only wait for a short time before you automatically return to your last waypoint.


Either way, you return to the game with full health and spirit. You don't lose any experience or items for being defeated.


__PROTECTED_77__REVIVE Defeated Heroes__PROTECTED_78__
You can __PROTECTED_79__left-click__PROTECTED_80__ on another player's defeated hero to revive that character.



__PROTECTED_81__Pick Up ORBS__PROTECTED_82__
When you defeat enemies, they sometimes drop colored orbs that can be picked up by moving over them. All orbs (except __PROTECTED_296__ ones) are visible to every player in the area, so any player can pick them up.


Different colored orbs have different effects:
- __PROTECTED_83__Red orbs__PROTECTED_84__ replenish your health
- __PROTECTED_85__Blue orbs__PROTECTED_86__ replenish your spirit
- __PROTECTED_87__Purple orbs__PROTECTED_88__ replenish both health and spirit
- __PROTECTED_89__Green orbs__PROTECTED_90__ give you bonus experience points
- __PROTECTED_91__Infinity orbs__PROTECTED_92__ give you experience towards your next Infinity Point

__PROTECTED_93__Watch Out! Orbs shrink over time__PROTECTED_94__
All orbs will shrink over time, which reduces their benefit. Pick up orbs as soon as you can!


__PROTECTED_95__Pick up ITEMS__PROTECTED_96__
Defeated enemies often drop items that you can equip to improve your abilities.


__PROTECTED_97____PROTECTED_4____PROTECTED_98__ an item to pick it up. If your __PROTECTED_99__inventory__PROTECTED_100__ is full, you can't pick up more items until you clear some room.

__PROTECTED_101__Tip! Remember Bodyslide__PROTECTED_102__
Because Bodyslide will take you back to your last HUB, it's a convenient way to swing buy a STASH, make some room for your items, then Bodyslide back into the action right where you left off. 

__PROTECTED_103__Tip! Items are for you only__PROTECTED_104__
Items dropped by enemies or destroyed objects are only visible to you, so no other player can pick them up. However, if you drop an item on the ground, it can thereafter be picked up by other players.

__PROTECTED_105__EQUIP Items on the Character Panel__PROTECTED_106__
Most items must be __PROTECTED_107__equipped__PROTECTED_108__ to provide any benefit. To open your inventory, __PROTECTED_109__left-click__PROTECTED_110__ on the character icon on the bottom left of the screen (it looks like a little person), or press __PROTECTED_111__I__PROTECTED_112__.


This panel shows your inventory as well as the items you've equipped in your __PROTECTED_113__equipment slots__PROTECTED_114__ (at the top right, surrounding the portrait of your hero).


__PROTECTED_115__Tip! Item details__PROTECTED_116__
__PROTECTED_117__Mouse over__PROTECTED_118__ an item in your inventory to see more details about it.


You can equip an item by __PROTECTED_119____PROTECTED_5____PROTECTED_120__ on it. This automatically equips the item in the correct slot. If another item already occupies that slot, equipping a new item moves the older item to your inventory.


__PROTECTED_121__Tip! Minimum level__PROTECTED_122__
Most items require a minimum level to equip them. If the item has a __PROTECTED_303__ box around it, you can't equip it yet. __PROTECTED_123__Mouse over__PROTECTED_124__ the item to see its minimum level.

__PROTECTED_129__Changing COSTUMES__PROTECTED_130__
Your hero starts with a __PROTECTED_131__costume__PROTECTED_132__ that's familiar and iconic to that character, but there are many other costumes to choose from! You can get more costumes either by finding them as rare drops from defeated enemies, inside Fortune Cards, or by purchasing them from our store. Press __PROTECTED_133__X__PROTECTED_134__ to visit the store.

__PROTECTED_137__BUYING, SELLING, DONATING, and STORING Items__PROTECTED_138__
Visit an Armor Vendor or Weapon Vendor to buy new items for your hero. The vendor always offers items that your hero can use.


You can also sell unwanted items to vendors to earn credits. If you accidentally sell an item, you can recover it from the vendor's buyback tab.


Instead of selling unwanted items, you can __PROTECTED_139__donate__PROTECTED_140__ them to a vendor or crafter. Donating items increases the rank of that vendor, allowing them to offer you items of better rarity (or in the case of a crafter, better recipes). Use __PROTECTED_141__ALT-right-click__PROTECTED_142__ to donate an item quickly: but be careful, you can't take back a donation!


__PROTECTED_143__Tip! Use the Refresh Button__PROTECTED_144__
If you don't see anything in the vendor panel that you like, press the Refresh button to see a new selection of items. This is also necessary if you've switched heroes recently, because the vendor may offer you gear for your previous hero.


__PROTECTED_145__Tip! Vendor types__PROTECTED_146__
There are three crucial vendor types: __PROTECTED_147__Weapon Vendors__PROTECTED_148__, __PROTECTED_149__Armor Vendors__PROTECTED_150__, and __PROTECTED_151__Crafters__PROTECTED_152__. When you increase the __PROTECTED_153__rank__PROTECTED_154__ of a vendor, all vendors of that type improve regardless of where they're located.


__PROTECTED_155__STORING Items__PROTECTED_156__
If you don't want to sell or donate an item, but it's taking up too much room in your inventory, you can store it in your __PROTECTED_157__S.T.A.S.H.__PROTECTED_158__, which is located in Avengers Tower (and other bases).


The __PROTECTED_290__. is separated into several tabs to help organize your stored items:
- General tabs can hold any item.
- Character tabs can hold only items for that specific character, such as a Bow for Hawkeye.


__PROTECTED_159__Right-clicking__PROTECTED_160__ an item in your inventory while the __PROTECTED_291__. is open places that item into a General tab.
To place an item into a different tab, __PROTECTED_161__left-click and drag__PROTECTED_162__ that item into the desired tab.


Most __PROTECTED_292__. Tabs are locked until you spend __PROTECTED_163__Gs__PROTECTED_164__ to unlock them for use.


__PROTECTED_165__MISSIONS and EVENTS__PROTECTED_166__
Your hero can receive a variety of __PROTECTED_167__missions__PROTECTED_168__ that allow you to explore the story of the game. You can view your __PROTECTED_169__mission log__PROTECTED_170__ by pressing __PROTECTED_171__L__PROTECTED_172__, or you can just follow crucial mission objectives by looking for a yellow arrow on the border of the screen.


You'll also encounter a variety of __PROTECTED_173__events__PROTECTED_174__, indicated by on-screen announcements and __PROTECTED_304__ arrows along the border of the screen. Events usually require the assistance of multiple heroes, so don't hesitate to jump in and help out!

__PROTECTED_175__Legendary Quests__PROTECTED_176__
Once you reach level 20, Odin himself will task you with specific objectives. Completing these quests will reward you with credits and Odin Marks. Additionally, each day there are Shared Legendary Quests, and even a Weekly Quest that reward you with caches of loot! 

__PROTECTED_177__Tip! Mission Tracker__PROTECTED_178__
On the right side of the screen is a Mission Tracker that keeps you informed of your quest progress.

 You can even track specific achievements by going into the Achievement tab. 

__PROTECTED_179__Gain EXPERIENCE to LEVEL UP__PROTECTED_180__
Level up by earning __PROTECTED_181__experience points__PROTECTED_182__ (abbreviated __PROTECTED_183__XP__PROTECTED_184__). As you gain XP, the __PROTECTED_297__ bar above your action bar fills up. When it fills completely, you gain a level.

__PROTECTED_185__Tip! Synegies!__PROTECTED_186__
At levels 25 and 50 you gain access to your current hero's Synergy skills. These are all passive buffs that can be shared with your other heroes for even more power! You can have up to 10 Synergy skills active at one. 


Gaining levels improves your hero in a variety of ways:
- Increases maximum health and spirit
- Unlocks new __PROTECTED_187__powers__PROTECTED_188__
- Unlocks new __PROTECTED_189__talents__PROTECTED_190__ to alter or improve your powers
- Increases __PROTECTED_191__attributes__PROTECTED_192__

__PROTECTED_193__INFINITY System__PROTECTED_194__
While you level you also gain experience for The Infinity System. Once your first hero becomes level 60 you will unlock the Infinity System. This system presents six Infinity Gems, themed accordingly from the Marvel Universe: Mind, Power, Reality, Soul, Space, and Time. Within each of the six Infinity Gems, you will be presented with five options, and you will allot your points based on what you want to emphasize in your play style.

__PROTECTED_195__Tip! Shared XP__PROTECTED_196__
So long as you're dealing damage in combat, you get XP for all enemies defeated nearby, even if another hero defeats them.


__PROTECTED_197__Use Your ACTION BAR__PROTECTED_198__
On the bottom center of the screen is your __PROTECTED_199__action bar__PROTECTED_200__, made up of eight empty slots. 
- To add a power to your action bar, drag that power from your power panel into the desired slot.
- To add an item to your action bar, drag that item from your inventory into the desired slot.


The slots on the far left and far right of the action bar are for your left and right mouse buttons, respectively. These slots start with powers assigned to them, but you can assign new powers to these slots if desired.


While that selection is open, you can __PROTECTED_201__left-click__PROTECTED_202__ on any power shown to instantly slot that power there.


__PROTECTED_203__Unlocking POWERS__PROTECTED_204__
Every hero has a unique set of powers that can be  seen on the power panel. To open the power panel, click on the power icon on the bottom left of screen (it looks like a star burst), or press __PROTECTED_6__ PowerLibraryPanel__PROTECTED_7__


__PROTECTED_205__Mouse-over__PROTECTED_206__ any power to see a description of it.

__PROTECTED_207__Tip! Assign your active powers__PROTECTED_208__
When you unlock a new active power, be sure to drag it to your action bar so you can use it.


__PROTECTED_209__TRAITS__PROTECTED_210__
Most heroes come with three Traits: One offensive, one defensive and one tailored to your hero. These tailored traits can grant things like a secondary resource, team buff, and even passive powers for your hero.


__PROTECTED_211__Tip! Archetypes__PROTECTED_212__
Every Hero has an Offensive and Defensive Archetype, as a component of their traits.

Offensive Archetype - Defines two specific Attributes that grant the Hero additional bonus Damage from accumulating it from Gear, Synergies, etc.

Defensive Archetype - Defines the defensive stat(s) that the Hero enjoys the most benefit from. These stats come from your Gear, the Infinity system, etc.



__PROTECTED_213__Unlocking TALENTS__PROTECTED_214__


After you've unlocked all of your Powers, you can begin to unlock Talents. Your first Talent choice unlocks at level 32. Talents are a way for you to have direct control on how your hero plays based on your preferences. Talents interact with your Powers in various ways depending on your hero. Some Talents can even change a Power into another Power entirely.


__PROTECTED_215__Find More HEROES__PROTECTED_216__

__PROTECTED_251__Form a SUPERGROUP__PROTECTED_252__
A supergroup is a lasting alliance between a group of players. You can acquire a Supergroup Sanction from __PROTECTED_253__War Machine__PROTECTED_254__ in Avengers Tower, which allows you to submit a request to form a basic supergroup.


Use these chat commands to operate your supergroup:
/sg: Send a message to all members of your supergroup.
/sgcreate: Submit a request to form a new supergroup.
/sginvite: Invite a new player to the supergroup.
/sgkick: Remove a member from your supergroup.
/sgpromote: Promote a supergroup member to an officer.
/sgdemote: Demote a supergroup officer to a member, or remove a member from the supergroup.
/sgrename: Submit a request to change your supergroup's name.
/sgleave: Leave your supergroup.

Experiencing terrigenesis before he was born, Blackagar Boltagon was granted frighteningly destructive powers. With a voice strong enough to destroy whole worlds, his parents would isolate and teach him to control his abilities. Finding silent companionship in one of his few visitors, Medusalith Amaquelin, the two's romance would blossom into marriage.

But when Blackagar used his voice to protect the city, many lives of the Inhumans' leading council were lost—including his parents. Blackagar reluctantly inherited the mantle of King of the Inhumans with Medusalith at his side. Though he justly serves the people of Attilan through the wise words his council, he choses his own words to protect Attilan from those who would put the Inhumans in danger.

1855369380788045070.String: Warren Worthington III, aka Angel, was a founding member of the X-Men and spent his earliest years as a mutant training under Professor Charles Xavier. But as with all students, the original X-Men strove to make a way for themselves out from under their teacher. Masquerading as the mutant hunters X-Factor, they hoped to find young mutants that needed their help before more sinister forces could reach them. Under just such an operation, Warren lost both his wings. Sensing his desperation, the villain Apocalypse offered Warren new wings under the condition that he would serve him as his Horseman of Death. Agreeing to the terms, Angel was no more, and the violent Archangel was let loose upon the world to rain razor sharp death from above!

- Bônus de experiência servem para Pontos Ômega.

- Heróis podem resetar Pontos Ômega alocados a qualquer momento.

- Clicar com shift aumenta um benefício em 10 graduações.

2001942153436333314.String: It was a cold day in December when Ultron became self-aware. Hank Pym had no idea exactly what consequences the machine's sentience would unleash on the world. But before the brilliant Avenger could act, Ultron rebelled. Not just against its creator, but against all organic life. Over time, Ultron has upgraded and rebuilt itself continually while pushing the evolutionary boundaries of synthetic life. Each step brings Ultron closer to perfection. But Earth's mightiest heroes, the Avengers, have always pulled the plug on Ultron's campaigns. Now Ultron's prime directive has been updated, taking this machine's unlimited functionality to unstoppable levels.

3594748814026999050.String:
Welcome to the Danger Room, __PROTECTED_0__. 

If you are perplexed, you can always return to me if you need a refresher.
Now, let us get started.

The area you are in now is the launching pad for all of the training simulations you will be running. Bring your Scenario Chips here and activate them to get started. Activating one will destroy the chip in the process and create a portal to your Scenario. Don't fret, Danger Room Scenarios are designed to be ran frequently so there are plenty of Chips out there for you to find and experience.

Scenarios are designed to be a challenge. As you will find, each Scenario Chip has data stored upon it that will dictate what sort of challenges you will face. Very few Scenarios will run the same. Your Scenario's data can be viewed on the Chip itself before you activate it, on the created Scenario's portal itself, and, lastly, as a reminder when you're running the Scenario, in your Mission Tracker panel.

There is much more to learn but I'll let Danger herself take over from here. She will walk you through how a Scenario might feel and what it will take to be successful.

Take this Training Scenario Chip and get started. Best of luck to you and your training, __PROTECTED_1__.

You're asking ME for stories about the Avengers? Yeah, I suppose I have a few of those.


The first time I met the Avengers, I punched Scarlet Witch in the face. It's a long story...let's just say I wasn't myself that day. After it all got sorted out, I had the opportunity to work with the team as a __PROTECTED_2__. liaison, but instead I got out of the super hero biz for a while.

A couple years later I got introduced to the team via Luke Cage. At this point they had all kinds of folks hanging out here in the tower: Spider-Man, Doctor Strange, Sentry, Spider-Woman...even Wolverine!

But even though they seemed to be letting almost anyone join, I never really felt like an Avenger. I fought alongside them a couple of times, and I'm not saying I embarrassed myself, but all that did was further convince me I wasn't the costumed crimefighter type.
